{"title": "Potential legal immigrants to undergo in-person interviews", "url": "http://nypost.com/2017/08/27/potential-legal-immigrants-to-undergo-in-person-interviews/", "text": "Potential legal immigrants will undergo in-person interviews with US Citizenship and Immigration Services workers as part of President Trump\u2019s \u201cextreme vetting\u201d efforts, Politico reported Saturday.\n\nThe new requirement, set to take effect Oct. 1, will likely slow the immigration application process and could reduce the number of new legal arrivals.\n\nThe in-person interview requirement is \u201cpart of a comprehensive strategy to further improve the detection and prevention of fraud and security risks to the United States,\u201d said Carter Langston, a spokesperson for Citizenship and Immigration Services.\n\nInterviews are already part of immigration process under the law, and conducting them was standard policy up to a decade ago. But in the last 10 years, the requirement has been routinely waived to shorten wait times for applicants.\n\nMeanwhile, the Trump administration appeared to be on the verge of rescinding the controversial DACA program \u2014 a set of legal protections for \u201cDreamers,\u201d illegal immigrants who were brought to the United States as children.", "source": "New York Post", "publish_date": "2017-08-27", "type": "article"}